VExtolling Hindolam
p3
sVnews
p4
VR aga Hindolam took centre stage at the &#8216;Oru Ragam Pala Bhavam' concert at the Kalikkotta Palace, Tripunithura. Myriad nuances of the raga were highlighted using many forms of music.The first among those on the first day was a Sopanasangeetham recital by Muraleedhara Marar. He sang a short kirtana in Hindolam. Next was a Kathakali music recital by Rajesh Babu.The artiste rendered &#8216;Enthiha man maanase,' a popular padam from &#8216;Karnasapatham,' followed by &#8216;Indhana sampaadana anantharam,' a piece from &#8216;Kuchelavritham.' Kalanilayam Ratheesh (chenda) and Kalanilayama Manoj (maddalam) supported him aptly.After the Kathakali music, there were light numbers and film music by Ganesh Sundaram. He sang &#8216;Viswamohini Jagadambike,' &#8216;Otakkuzhalvili ozhukiyozhuki varum,' &#8216;Chandana mani vaathil' and &#8216;Kaavyapusthakamallo jeevitham,' among others.Raga MalkaunsA session on Hindustani music was followed by Hari Alancode on the santoor and Dean Mohan on the tabla. Hari was able to play the alaap elaborately in a short kriti in raag Malkauns, which is similar to Hindolam.The day's programme culminated in a Carnatic concert by Cherthala K.N. Ranganatha Sarma. In Hindolam, he sang &#8216;Maa Ramanan Uma Ramanan' and &#8216;Samaganalolane' both by Papanasam Sivan, and a ragam-tanam-pallavi, &#8216;Nee Padamulegathi,' with niraval in Hamsaanandi, Surutti, Behag and Kharaharapriya.Ranganatha Sarma also rendered some other songs in different ragas such as &#8216;Ninne Bhajana Seyu' by Tyagaraja (Natta), &#8216;Smarane ondesaalade' by Purandaradasa (Malayamarutham), &#8216;Bhaja bhaja maanasa Raghavendram' (Jayanthi) and a virutham &#8211; &#8216;Sivassakthyaayukthaa' from &#8216;Soundaryalahari' before the mangalam. R. Swaminathan (violin), Palladam Ravi (mridangam) and Thrissur Sreejith (ghatom) accompanied him.Sudha Raghunathan performed on the second day of the fete. She commenced the concert with a Hamsadhwani varnam, which was followed by &#8216;Siddhivinayakam' (Shanmukhapriya) by Dikshitar. Sudha described the rare raga Veera Vasantham, which is the janyam of 24th melakartha, Varunapriya. She also gave a short alaap in this.&#8216;Nannu brova lalitha' (Lalitha) by Syama Sastri was mellifluous. This was followed by the short kritis &#8216;Sree Venkata Gireesam' (Suruti) by Dikshithar and &#8216;Unnadiye Gathi' (Bahudari) by GNB.Erudite skillsWith the alaap of Kharaharapriya &#8211; the main raga of the day, Sudha mesmerised the audience with her erudite skills. The Tyagaraja kriti &#8216;Chakkani Raja' was a good selection for such a type of baani. Violinist B.V. Raghavendra Rao followed her with ease. The niraval and swaram were aptly sung, which made the rendering of the main raga complete in every sense. Tani was by Madippakkam Suresh (mridangam), R. Raman (ghatam) and T.H. Subhash Chandran ( morsing).The thukkadas also captivated rasikas by giving off a serene vibe. She sang &#8216;Kuzhal ondrum illai' by C. Rajagopalachari in ragamalika, &#8216;Muddugari Yasoda by Annamacharya (Kurinchi), which is one of the vocalist's masterpieces, &#8216;Jagadodhaarana' by Purandaradasar (Kapi), &#8216;Kandenaan,' a Sai Bhajan and &#8216;Chinna chiru kiliye' (Bhairavi) by Subrahmania Bharati. Before concluding the concert, she sang a thillana by Lalgudi.The concerts were organised by Sree Poornathrayeesa Sangeetha Sabha in connection with its 35th anniversary celebrations
